---
import Base from "../../layouts/Base.astro";
---

<Base
  title="Public API"
  description="Documentation for the kapadiya.net public content API and WebMCP tools."
>
  <section class="py-18 border-t border-border-medium">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-[900px] px-6 sm:px-12">
      <div class="mb-12 border-b border-border-soft pb-6">
        <div class="mb-3 text-xs font-medium tracking-widest uppercase text-ind-accent">
          Agent access
        </div>
        <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight uppercase text-text-primary">
          Public content API
        </h1>
        <p class="mt-4 max-w-[680px] text-sm leading-relaxed text-text-muted">
          Read-only profile, project, and writing metadata. No account, API key,
          or OAuth token is required.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="blog-prose space-y-10 text-text-secondary">
        <section>
          <h2 class="mb-4 text-2xl font-semibold text-text-primary">Endpoints</h2>
          <ul class="space-y-3 font-mono text-sm">
            <li><a href="/api/profile.json">GET /api/profile.json</a></li>
            <li><a href="/api/posts.json">GET /api/posts.json</a></li>
            <li><a href="/api/status">GET /api/status</a></li>
            <li><a href="/openapi.json">GET /openapi.json</a></li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="mb-4 text-2xl font-semibold text-text-primary">WebMCP</h2>
          <p>
            Pages register read-only browser tools for the public profile, blog
            links, and visible-content search through WebMCP. This static site
            does not advertise a remote MCP server.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="mb-4 text-2xl font-semibold text-text-primary">
            Authentication and usage
          </h2>
          <p>
            All operations are public and read-only. Agents use the anonymous
            registration profile and receive no credential. See
            <a href="/auth.md">auth.md</a> and the
            <a href="/.well-known/oauth-authorization-server">authorization-server metadata</a>
            for machine-readable guidance.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-3">
            Content may be used for search and as agent input, but not for model
            training. The same preference is published in <a href="/robots.txt">robots.txt</a>.
          </p>
        </section>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>
